Questions:
What is the primary objective of the research study titled "A Phase II Randomized Controlled Double-Blind Clinical Trial of Sphenopalatine Ganglion Blocks for Headache after Concussion"?
A) To compare the effectiveness of two different surgical procedures for treating concussions;
B) To assess the safety and efficacy of sphenopalatine ganglion blocks in improving headaches after a concussion;
C) To determine the long-term effects of concussion on cognitive function;
D) To evaluate the use of over-the-counter medications in the treatment of post-concussion symptoms.

Correct answer: B

What will happen if you choose to withdraw from the "Sphenopalatine Ganglion Blocks for Headache after Concussion" study before its completion?
A) You will be required to pay a penalty fee for early withdrawal; 
B) You will lose access to all medical care provided by the University of Michigan;
C) You will not face any penalties and will retain your entitled benefits;
D) Your health insurance will be canceled as a result of your withdrawal.

Correct answer: C

If you choose not to participate in the "Sphenopalatine Ganglion Blocks for Headache after Concussion" study, what standard care options are available for treating your headaches?
A) You may be advised to rest and avoid activities that aggravate your headaches; 
B) You may receive alternative medical treatments such as over-the-counter medications, prescription medications, physical therapy, or exercise as recommended by your doctor;
C) You will be required to participate in a different clinical trial;
D) No other treatments will be available outside of the study.

Correct answer: B

How will your personal health information be handled in this study according to the consent form?
A) Your health information will be shared publicly on the study's website; 
B) Your health information will be kept in a separate research file without identifiers and may be shared with other researchers without additional consent;
C) Your health information will be disclosed to anyone who requests it for any reason;
D) Your health information will be used for marketing purposes by the sponsoring company.

Correct answer: B
